# =============================================================================
# dnstoys — Kailash Nadh's "A DNS server that offers useful
#           utilities and services over the DNS protocol" — a Go
#           DNS server that responds to specially-formed DNS
#           queries with utility values: weather forecasts, world
#           time, currency conversion, unit conversion, IP
#           lookups, IFSC bank code lookups, dictionary
#           definitions, UUIDs, dice rolls, sudoku puzzles,
#           random numbers, base conversions, CIDR computations,
#           air quality index, aerial astronomy, coin flips,
#           DigiPin postal codes, epoch conversion, excuses,
#           foreign exchange rates, nanoids, number-to-words,
#           sky observations, timezone lookups, vitamin
#           information.
#           Distinguishing from every other DNS server (BIND,
#           PowerDNS, Knot, Unbound, CoreDNS) by:
#             - HTTP-LIKE INFORMATION SERVICES via DNS — queries
#               like `dig weather.tokyo @dns.toys` return weather
#               TXT records; works through ANY DNS-capable client
#               (curl, dig, nslookup, browsers, IoT devices)
#             - 23+ INTEGRATED SERVICES: each service has its own
#               internal/services/<name>/ package implementing a
#               handler trait
#             - SNAPSHOT PERSISTENCE: services like fx (forex
#               rates) periodically dump their state to disk on
#               SIGTERM/SIGHUP for restart-safe operation
#             - SIGUNUSED HOT-RELOAD: receives SIGUNUSED (signal
#               31) to dump snapshots without shutting down
#             - SINGLE-BINARY DEPLOYMENT: ships as one statically-
#               linked Go binary deployable on resource-constrained
#               infrastructure (DNS protocol is UDP-light)
#             - knadh/koanf LAYERED CONFIGURATION: TOML config
#               file(s) via --config (StringSlice, repeatable) +
#               pflag overrides via koanf/providers/posflag
#               integration; per-service [service.name] sections
#               with .enabled / .snapshot_enabled / .snapshot_file
#               keys
#             - DOGFOODING NARRATIVE: dnstoys is by Kailash Nadh
#               (knadh on GitHub) — the SAME AUTHOR as the
#               headline library being documented here
#               (knadh/koanf), making this a "tool eating its own
